Ad [Addendum] Good Shepherd (formerly Princeton) when in Princeton published by Glück (Jb. Wien, N.F. IX, 1935, p. 164, Abb. III as P.B. the Younger. Glück mention replica in F. Pollack Coll. Vienna (signed, panel 38 x 58 cm). The recent cleaning seems to have been rather sharp e.g. the flying bird!; J. Brueghel after Dürer: Madonna with Many Animals, Doria. The fox's skin very similar to the wolf in Good Shepherd.
